reviewText: wonderful selection of preschool stories gently told and presented, but why less than ten percent in Spanish? I wish they all had a SPanish track as well.Great to see the immortal and universally enjoyed Ezra Jack Keats here so well represented with Whistle for Willie, SNowy DAy and PEter, and half of the Spanish versions are from Keats.
summary: fifty classic tales from this excellent patient and gentle series but why less than ten percent in SPanish?
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: My kids like some of these and not others, I think each child will be the same. These are not all great, some of them are even bad, but there are a lot and I promise that your kids 4 and under will like some of them. I will note that I paid 15 bucks for this set so it was way worth it. I would not pay over $30. So keep in mind the price.
summary: Great deal if you can get it under $20
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: This is our toddlers least favorite of them all.  She likes some of the stories but others she gets bored.  It may be the age.  She is 2 1/2.  She is more into the video books that have added music and have songs made by Scholastic like "Wheels on the bus."
summary: We own a lot of these story dvds
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: good little videos which the kids enjoy. THey are fun, easy to understand and the kids really enjoy the variety.
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: Anyone who works with children should purchase these collections, they are without a doubt a real treasure.  Each story is as different as the next, uniquely told with it's own style of annimation.  The stories leave you wanting more and more...you can't get enough......That is why I've bought so many.......they will genuinely keep you and your child's interest...
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: I bought it for my nephew who thoroughly enjoyed all the stories.  My favorite was the DVD on bed night stories it did make him sleepy!!!!!
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures

reviewText: There are so many stories in this little box!  It truly is a video library.  Some of the stories are animated.  Corduroy is a short film!  Children will recognize many of the selections as books they've read (which they find very exciting).  A few of the titles aren't that exciting, and require adult guidance to keep children focused, and learning.  Overall, this was a great investment!
Title: My Very First Treasury of 50 Storybook Classics: Preschool Stories Scholastic Storybook Treasures
